@node MAIN "Physical objects handled by ASense"

  @{i}Note@{ui}: This guide is an auxiliary part of ASense package.It describes
  the solar system and surrounding stars in great and up-to-date details
  from the @{b}astronomical@{ub} point of view.

  @{"Definition" link ASENSE-SELECT-PL-DEF} of a planet (IAU, 24-Aug-2006)
  @{"Planets" link ASENSE-SELECT-PLANETS} (planets and luminaries)
  @{"Minor Planets" link ASENSE-SELECT-ASTEROIDS} (asteroids and comets)
  @{"Delineation" link ASENSE-PLANETS-DELINEATION} of the newly discovered planets and planetoids (@{b}astrol.@{ub} essay)

  @{"Stars" link ASENSE-SELECT-STARS} (detailed analysis of stars)

@{b}@{u}Acknowledgements@{uu}@{ub}:
  - This research has made use of the SIMBAD database, operated at CDS,
    Strasbourg, France.

@{b}@{u}Links@{uu}@{ub}:
