    @{b}Cordelia@{ub} was named after a daughter of King Lear in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}King Lear@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon that acts as the @{i}inner@{ui} shepherding
      satellite for Uranus's epsilon ring.
    @{b}Ophelia@{ub} was named after a daughter of Polonius in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}Hamlet@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon that acts as the @{i}outer@{ui} shepherding
      satellite for Uranus's epsilon ring.
    @{b}Bianca@{ub} was named after a sister of Katherine in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}The Taming of the Shrew@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon.
    @{b}Cressida@{ub} was named after a daughter of Calchas in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}Troilus and Cressida@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon.
    @{b}Desdemona@{ub} was named after the wife of Othello in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}Othello@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon.
    @{b}Juliet@{ub} was named after the tragic heroine in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}Romeo and Juliet@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon.
    @{b}Portia@{ub} was named after a rich heiress in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}Merchant of Venice@{ui}'.It is a rocky moon.
    @{b}Rosalind@{ub} was named after a daughter of the banished Duke in
      Shakespeare's play '@{i}As you like it@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon.
    @{b}Belinda@{ub} was named after a heroine in Alexander Pope's
      '@{i}The Rape of the Lock@{ui}'.It is a small rocky moon.
    @{b}Puck@{ub} was named after a mischievous fairy in Shakespeare's play
      '@{i}Midsummer Night's Dream@{ui}'.It is a rocky moon.

    @{b}Miranda@{ub} [mih-RAN-dah] is one of the strangest bodies in the solar
      system.The moon consists of huge fault canyons upto 20 km deep,
      terraced layers and a mixture of old and young surfaces.Younger
      region may be the result of incomplete differentiation of the
      moon into layers, or perhaps Miranda was once broken into pieces
      by an impact, and undergone a reaggregation afterward.Actually
      scientists believe that this could have happened upto 5 times !
        The moon has extra large tectonic activity, in comparison with
      it's small size and low temperature (86 K).There are signs of icy
      flows and it is believed that an additional heat source, like tidal
      heating must be involved.@{i}@{b}Miranda is just about as big as it must
      be in order to be round@{ub}@{ui}.Voyager 2 flew just 31 Mm from it's surface.
        Miranda was named after the daughter of magician Prospero in
      Shakespeare's play '@{i}The Tempest@{ui}'.

    @{b}Ariel@{ub} [AIR-ee-al] has the brightest and also the youngest surface,
      one devoid of all craters greater than 50 km in diameter.Larger,
      older craters were obliterated.There are also many fault valleys
      and signs of extensive flows of icy material.Valley floors have
      been covered with younger icy flows.The substance that have caused
      those flaws couldn't have been water, because water is strong like
      steel on Ariel's deep subzero temperatures.Instead, it might have
      been the fluid made of ammonia, methane or even carbon monoxide.

    @{b}Umbriel@{ub} [UM-bree-ul] is dark and ancient with many large craters.
    @{b}Titania@{ub} [Ty-TAY-ne-ah] is the largest satellite of Uranus.It shows
      signs of some previous geological activity (canyons).
    @{b}Oberon@{ub} [O-buh-ron] has old, heavily cratered icy surface.Some unknown
      dark material covers the floors of many craters.

    @{b}Caliban@{ub} is an irregular satellite, 98 km in diameter.It is a captured
      body that orbits in a retrograde direction 7.2 Gm away from Uranus.
      The moon's orbit is eccentric and highly inclined.The satellite has
      an unusually red color, which may suggest a Kuiper-Belt origin.It
      is probably a mixture of rocks and ice.
        Caliban has been named after a savage and deformed slave of the
      magician Prospero in the Shakespeare's play '@{i}The Tempest@{ui}'.He is the
      son of witch Sycorax who imprisoned the fairy Ariel for disobediance.
      Prospero frees Ariel from Sycorax's spell and enslaves Caliban.
    @{b}Stephano@{ub} is a small moonlet, named after a butler in the Shakespeare's
      play '@{i}The Tempest@{ui}'.
    @{b}Trinculo@{ub} is a small moonlet, some 10 km in diameter, discovered by the
     same people that discovered the rest of the irregular Uranian moons
     (@{i}Gladman, Holman, Kavelaars, Petit et al@{ui}.).
    @{b}Sycorax@{ub} is an irregular satellite, 190 km in diameter.It is a captured
      body that orbits in a retrograde direction 12.2 Gm away from Uranus.
      The moon's orbit is highly eccentric and highly inclined.The satellite
      has an unusually red color, which may suggest a Kuiper-Belt origin.It
      is probably a mixture of rocks and ice.
        Sycorax has been named after a witch who imprisoned the fairy Ariel
      for disobediance in the Shakespeare's play '@{i}The Tempest@{ui}'.
    @{b}Prospero@{ub} and @{b}Setebus@{ub} are small satellites, named after characters in the
      Shakespeare's play '@{i}The Tempest@{ui}'.Prospero is a powerful magician, and
      Setebus is a god of Sycorax, the witch.

  @{b}@{u}Properties of Uranus@{uu}@{ub}:
              mass: 8.686e25 kg (14.535 Earth's)
     equ. diameter: 51.118 Mm (4.0074 Earth's)
    polar diameter: 49.946 Mm
   sidereal period: 84.011 yr (30685.4 d)
