                                                                                                      instant fusion of a VII occurs when it breaches the 1.4 sun-mass limit; there are no remnants afterwards; wavelength
                                                                                                      distribution and luminosities are therefore almost identical from case to case, which allows them to serve as candles;
                                                                                                      debris appear in clumps; shockwave bubble shows continuous arcs; initial fading of 0.1 mag/day slows to 0.014 mag/day
